column2: Arrows have straight sides and a pointy end
Arrows point at something
Both ends of a line are called points
Circles are round
Crescents have two round sides and pointy ends
Diamonds have four flat sides the same length with pointy corners at both ends
Ellipses are round and look like circles but flatter
Everywhere on a circle is the same distance from its center
Geometric Shapes
Hearts have two round sides and a pointy corner at the bottom
Hexagons have six flat sides the same length
Lines go straight from one end to the other
Octagons have eight flat sides the same length
Ovals are round and look like circles but flatter
Pentagons have five flat sides the same length
Points are tiny dots
Rectangles have four flat sides
Rhombuses have four flat sides the same length with pointy corners at both ends
Rings have one circle inside another circle
Semi-circles are half of a circle
Squares have four flat sides the same length
Stars have pointy corners that stick out
Trapezoids have four flat sides
Triangles have three flat sides
